        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <p>I built this site for two purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>to access my programming notes from anywhere</li>
          <li>to experiment with CSS for fun</li>
        </ul>
        <p>I write concise articles that get straight to the point.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <p>
          I built this website with <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>.
          <br />
          Astro helps create fast web applications thanks to its <a
            href="/architecture/islands-architecture">Islands architecture</a
          >: it renders HTML and only sends JavaScript for interactive
          components when needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .home-container {
      position: relative;
      margin: 2em 0;
      min-height: 400px;
    }

    .home-copy {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0 24em;
    }

    .home-copy h1 {
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 1em;
      line-height: 1.3;
      text-align: center;
      position: relative;
    }

    .home-copy h1::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      transform: translateY(0.5em);
      left: 30%;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 40%;
      height: 4px;
      background: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    .home-copy p {
      font-size: 1.4em;
    }

    .home-copy .section:first-of-type {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .home-copy .section {
      margin-bottom: 2em;
    }

    @media (max-width: 1200px) {
      p {
        font-size: 1.2em;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 800px) {
      .home-container {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .home-copy {
        flex: 0;
        padding: 0 1em 2em 1em;
        text-align: center;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
